The paper deals with the problem of influence maximization in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS subfields. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which is specifically dedicated to research on social networks and their analysis. The paper also involves algorithms and optimization techniques, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of the independent cascade model and the analysis of approximation ratios could also place the paper under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
